  hexssence: {
    mishaps: {
      extraction: {
        valid_target: "valid Extraction target"
      },
      combine_vecs: {
        valid_list: "list of vectors pointing to Essence jars",
        valid_recipe: "valid combination recipe (is it in the right order?)"
      }
    },
    book: {
      patterns: {
        spells: {
          essence_spells: {
            title: "Essence Spells",
            desc: "I have discovered a number of patterns relating to $(l:items/essence)$(item)Essence/$, the fundamental components of items.",
            extract_essence: "Extracts the essence from a dropped item. Cost varies depending on target item.",
            combine_essence: {
              "1": "Remove a list of vectors, a list of numbers, and a vector from the stack, then take essences from the jars at the given locations, mix them according to the given quantitites, and summon the resulting item at the given location.$(br)",
              "2": "More specifically, for each vector in the first list, it will use the number at the corresponding index in the second list to determine how much essence to extract from the jar at that location.$(br)After essence has been extracted from all of the jars, the extracted essence will be combined to create an item at the given location. Mishaps if the given ratio of essences cannot be combined into any valid item.$(br2)Cost varies depending on the produced item.$(br)"
            }
          }
        },
      },
    },
    page: {
      essence: {
        "1": "Strange, some of these scrolls imply that basic $(item)items/$ such as cobblestone are $(italic)not/$ discrete forms, but are instead amalgamations of even baser $(item)Essences/$.",
        "2": "I wonder if I can $(l:patterns/spells/essence_spells)exploit this.../$",
        "jar": "I've devised a way to store a large quantity of any one Essence.$(br)To store an Essence in a jar, I can simply interact while holding a matching essence.$(br)Interacting again within a short timeframe deposits every matching essence in my inventory.$(br)Punching the jar with an empty hand or essence extracts one of the contained essences into my hand, and crouching as I do so extracts a full stack."
      }
    },
    entry: {
      items: "Essences"
    },
    tooltip: {
      essence_jar: "Stored: %s x%d"
    }
  },

